Corinthians Wins Brazilian Soccer Championship
RIO DE JANEIRO , December 23 ( Xinhua ) -- Corinthians won the Brazilian soccer championship on Wednesday , defeating Cruzeiro 2 - 0 in the third and final leg of the final .
Corinthians ' Edilson opened the scoring in the 65th minute and his teammate Marcelinho Carioca netted the second goal in the 83rd minute of the game .
The two teams drew 2 - 2 in the first leg of the final and tied 1 - 1 in the second .
Corinthians took the title with 5 - 3 win in aggregate .
